Study Title: Iressa vs Best Supportive Care - 2nd/3rd Line Survival Study
Brief Summary: This study is being carried out to see if adding ZD1839 to other standard supportive care is more effective than standard supportive care alone for the treatment of patients with NSCLC whose disease has recurred after previous chemotherapy treatment.
Primary Outcome Measures: The primary objective of this study is to compare overall survival for ZD1839 plus best supportive care versus placebo plus best supportive care
Secondary Outcome Measures: · ZD1839 + BSC versus Placebo + BSC in terms of time to treatment failure|· ZD1839 + BSC versus Placebo + BSC in terms of investigator assessed overall|· objective tumour response (CR + PR)|· ZD1839 + BSC versus Placebo + BSC in terms of tolerability|· ZD1839 + BSC versus Placebo + BSC in terms of quality of life changes
Study Design: Allocation: RANDOMIZED|Intervention Model: PARALLEL|Masking: DOUBLE|Primary Purpose: TREATMENT
